
= MODE =

=== DEFINITION ===

The Mode of an element defines the kind of element exploitation expected in given use conditions. A Mode is activated by operators. It is usually the result of a design decision and is an expected behavior feature of the element.


Mode changes are described with Transitions.


Example : Online test, Maintenance, Daily Servicing, nominal/operational, training...


